# Code conventions:

===============
===THIS YEAR===
===============
// RULE 		    => Follow Exactly (or else...?)
// GUIDELINE 	=> "Be Mindful Of ..."

1. RULE: Tabs not spaces, a tab is 4 spaces

2. RULE: English is the language of choice

3. NAMING RULE: Adhere to Engine / Tool / Language PascalCasing/camelCasing conventions
// TODO: Make sure you define which conventions you are adhering to in documentation

4. RULE: Curly bracket war ended in: Next Line.

5. RULE: Local variable definitions should be at the top of the function, if possible

6. GUIDELINE: Class names should be logical (singular) units

7. GUIDELINE: Method names should begin with a verb unless they can’t

// WHITESPACES
8. GUIDELINE: Group things that belong together (gray area) without whitespaces, and add whitespace between things that do not belong together
    RULE: When adding whitespaces, you should add only one.

9. RULE: Padding between () brackets, after commas, and around operators.
void SomeFunction( int x, int y, int z );
int x = y * z;
 
10. RULE: Order of declarations:
   - ORDER: public / protected / private
   - ORDER: member variables before functions
   - ORDER: Engine hook functions (BeginPlay, Start/Update, etc.) before custom functions
   - ORDER GUIDELINE: Try to place functions in the order of appearance as much as possible
   - INCLUSION: You must include access modifiers always (private/protected/public) when relevant

11. RULE: The word "bomboclaat" must feature in every script.

